    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>An ixtangi has an innate ability to change their coloration as a standard action; this produces one of the following effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Glimmer</strong>: The ixtangi flashes their coloration in a display that distracts onlookers. Enemies within 30 feet that can see the ixtangi must succeed at a DC Will save (DC = 10 + the ixtangi&rsquo;s Charisma modifier + half the ixtangi&rsquo;s level ) or be @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.7PPRS6krnvaTHbxh]{Fascinated} for 1d4 rounds. A creature can be affected by this ability only once per day. This is a mind-affecting effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Stealth</strong>: The ixtangi mimics their surroundings, becoming almost invisible. They gain a +2 racial bonus to Stealth checks to hide until the beginning of their next turn.</p>"
    },
